<br>
When a Dragon pops and its our turn, we dont have a choice of day to kill it. We have to engage, or  be preparing to, by 8pm Local time (KCoG used Eastern time) or we lose our turn. Most of our Dragon raids end up being on weeknights. Very rarely have I seen it fall on a weekend. Monday thru Saturday we have a gathering time of 8pm Eastern. We have people from all over the world come on raids, but we use the 5pm Pacific-8pm Eastern as a time frame that &quot;most&quot; people are off work after 5pm. Although we have ALOT of people that its 5 or 6 in the morning when we finish a Naggy raid, but they still choose to come.<br>
<br>
With Planes Raids, you can actually post a few choices for days to have them, sometimes you get your choice, sometimes you don't. I know since Destructress has taken over Planes raids, they have been on Sundays, starting in the early afternoon (Sunday Dragons also start in the afternoon).<br>
<br>
As far as holding other raids during the day or earlier on weekends, I know many, many times Ikada has run Plane of Growth raids on Sunday and Monday mornings.<br>
<br>
But a few people running raids, events, etc.. can only do so much. I know Destructress and I are both Leaders of active guilds besides being active with running our respective KCoG raids. I would love to see more mixer hunts, chess tourneys, etc.. sponsored by KCoG guilds, but not many people are willing to give of thier time for little to no reward.<br>
